Day 4 devops 90 days challenge

Q. what is kernel in linux?
ans- responsible for managing the system's hardware and software resources, providing essential services, and acting as an interface between the hardware and the user-level applications. heart of linux OS.

Q. what is shell in linux?
ans -  command-line interface (CLI) that allows users to interact with the operating system and execute commands. It is essentially a program that acts as an intermediary between the user and the Linux kernel, interpreting the commands entered by the user and executing them

Q. what is shell scripting in linux?
ans - series of commands in a text file that can be executed by the shell interpreter. The shell is a command-line interface that allows you to interact with the operating system and run various commands

q1. What is #!/bin/bash? can we write #!/bin/sh as well?
ans -#!/bin/bash is known as a "shebang. essential because it tells the system which interpreter to use when the script is run and should be executed in bash shell.
he main difference between #!/bin/bash and #!/bin/sh lies in the shell's features and compatibility. bash typically includes additional features and enhancements

q2. Write a Shell Script which prints I will complete #90DaysOofDevOps challenge?
ans - vim shellScript.sh (name of file)
#!/bin/bash
echo "I will complete #90DaysOofDevOps challenge"

q3. Write a Shell Script to take user input, input from arguments and print the variables.
ans - vim Userinput_arg.sh (name of file)
#!/bin/bash
echo "what is your age?"
read age
echo "my age is ${age}"

chmod 777 Userinput_arg.sh
./Userinput_arg.sh

q4.Write an Example of If else in Shell Scripting by comparing 2 numbers?
ans- vim ifElse.sh (name)

#!/bin/bash

echo "enter 1st num"
read num1
echo "enter 2nd num"
read num2

if["$num1" -eq "$num2"]; then
echo"num are equal"
elif["$num1" -gt "$num2"]; then
echo"num1 is greater"
else
echo "num2 is greater"
fi
